import pandas as pd
with open("Downloads/bank_additional_file.csv", "r", encoding="utf-8") as file:
    lines = file.readlines()
cleaned_data = [line.strip().replace('"', '').split(';')for line in lines]
df = pd.DataFrame(cleaned_data[1:], columns=cleaned_data[0])
if 'y' in df.columns:
    df.rename(columns={'y': 'deposit'}, inplace=True)

In [16]:
# Calculate the number of rows and columns for subplots
num_plots = len(cat_cols)
num_rows = (num_plots + 1) // 2  # Round up for odd number
num_cols = 2

# Create a new large figure
plt.figure(figsize=(24, 6 * num_rows))  # Wider & taller subplots

# Loop through each feature and create a large countplot
for i, feature in enumerate(cat_cols, 1):
    plt.subplot(num_rows, num_cols, i)
    sns.countplot(x=feature, data=df, palette='Wistia')
    plt.title(f'Bar Plot of {feature}', fontsize=20)
    plt.xlabel(feature, fontsize=16)
    plt.ylabel('Count', fontsize=16)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, fontsize=12)
    plt.yticks(fontsize=12)

#Adjust spacing between plots
plt.tight_layout(pad=4.0)  # Add padding between plots
plt.subplots_adjust(top=0.95)  # Optional: add some margin on top
plt.show()

import pandas as pd

# Specify target columns
cols = ['age', 'campaign', 'duration']

# Convert to numeric (coerce errors to NaN)
df[cols] = df[cols].apply(pd.to_numeric, errors='coerce')

# Drop rows with NaN values before calculating IQR (optional but safe)
df = df.dropna(subset=cols)

# Compute IQR
Q1 = df[cols].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = df[cols].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1

# Compute bounds
lower = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
upper = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

# Filter: Set outliers to NaN
df[cols] = df[cols].where((df[cols] >= lower) & (df[cols] <= upper))

# (Optional) Drop rows with outliers
# df.dropna(subset=cols, inplace=True)

In [50]:
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix,classification_report,accuracy_score

def eval_model(y_test,y_pred):
    acc=accuracy_score(y_test,y_pred)
    print('Accuracy_Score',acc)
    cm=confusion_matrix(y_test,y_pred)
    print('confusion matrix\n',cm)
    print('Classification Report\n',classification_report(y_test,y_pred))

def mscore(model):
    train_score=model.score(x_train,y_train)
    test_score=model.score(x_test,y_test)
    print('Training Score',train_score)
    print('Testing Score',test_score)
